{"word":"ἀκουστέον","slug":"ἀκουστέον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀκουστέον</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:ἀκούω'><el>ἀκούω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>one must hear</i> or <i>hearken to</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἀκουστέος, α, ον</el>, <i>to be hearkened to</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}